#. <section class="sutta" id="sn46.21"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn46.21:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 46"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 46"

#. </p><p>
#. VAR: 3. Udāyivagga → bodhanā (pts1)
msgctxt "sn46.21:0.2"
msgid "3. Udāyivagga"
msgstr "3. With Udāyī"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 21. Bodhāyasutta → udāyīvaggo (bj)
msgctxt "sn46.21:0.3"
msgid "21. Bodhāyasutta"
msgstr "21. To Awakening"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.21:1.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami … pe … ekamantaṃ "
"nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha … and said to him:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.21:2.1"
msgid "“‘Bojjhaṅgā, bojjhaṅgā’ti, bhante, vuccanti."
msgstr "“Sir, they speak of the ‘awakening factors’."

msgctxt "sn46.21:2.2"
msgid "Kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, ‘bojjhaṅgā’ti vuccantī”ti?"
msgstr "How are the awakening factors defined?”"

msgctxt "sn46.21:2.3"
msgid "“‘Bodhāya saṃvattantī’ti kho, bhikkhu, tasmā bojjhaṅgāti vuccanti."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicant, they’re called awakening factors because they lead to awakening."

msgctxt "sn46.21:2.4"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhu, satisambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ … pe … "
"upekkhāsambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ "
"vossaggapariṇāmiṃ."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant develops the awakening factors of mindfulness, investigation of "
"principles, energy, rapture, tranquility, immersion, and equanimity, which "
"rely on seclusion, fading away, and cessation, and ripen as letting go."

msgctxt "sn46.21:2.5"
msgid "‘Bodhāya saṃvattantī’ti kho, bhikkhu, tasmā ‘bojjhaṅgā’ti vuccantī”ti."
msgstr "They’re called awakening factors because they lead to awakening.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn46.21:2.6"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
